                                    for each ticket? Where is the Value?
The airline miles and credit card award industry is a very unorganized and complex group of partners and rules that are constantly changing. With our combined experience of over 20 years in the industry, we are able to filter out all the noise and get down to business. We understand how to leverage availability and partner airlines, to get the same flights at a much lower cost.
                                </p>
                                <br />
                                <h3>What about my credit card concierge service?</h3>
                                <p>
                                    Many of the major credit card programs have 24 hour concierge services that are there to assist you with your travel. These services can be great at finding options 
                                    for flights, hotels, cruises, etc. The downside is when you are ready to book, most credit card programs will allow you to redeem your rewards for travel, however it is usually at the full retail price. On top of that when redeeming your points, they only give you a 1 to 1 redemption rate. For example, a business class flight from LAX-CDG-LAX, could be at a price of $5,500. Your credit card might let you book this flight for points and require 550,000 points. THey will not tell you though, that it may be possible to transfer 125,000 of those points to the airline and book directly with them. This is only one example of course. <a href="Contact.aspx">Contact ETG</a>, and let one of our Gurus help you today!
                                </p>
